1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,920
It’s just the two of us left.

2
00:00:01,952 --> 00:00:02,936
I’m afraid

3
00:00:02,968 --> 00:00:05,304
you won’t be able to control yourself.

4
00:00:05,320 --> 00:00:07,300
You’re the one who won’t be able to control yourself.

5
00:00:07,320 --> 00:00:08,792
Ever since we walked into the house,

6
00:00:08,808 --> 00:00:10,790
your focus has only been on me.

7
00:00:11,208 --> 00:00:12,208
Phi.

8
00:00:12,710 --> 00:00:14,040
He’s my producer.

9
00:00:15,264 --> 00:00:17,260
I won’t let anyone steal him.

10
00:00:17,420 --> 00:00:19,048
Who’s your producer?

11
00:00:19,088 --> 00:00:20,340
Didn’t you kick me out?

12
00:00:20,544 --> 00:00:22,128
You kicked me out of your life,

13
00:00:22,160 --> 00:00:23,592
but you still keep those things.

14
00:00:23,624 --> 00:00:25,984
Don’t get the wrong idea that it’s the lip balm you got me.

15
00:00:29,310 --> 00:00:30,752
I have to taste it then.

16
00:00:53,500 --> 00:00:54,952
Were you secretly watching me?

17
00:00:56,280 --> 00:00:58,496
Phi, please!

18
00:01:00,180 --> 00:01:02,784
Waking up and secretly watching
your boyfriend’s face after sex?

19
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:04,720
You act like this is a romance movie.

20
00:01:08,070 --> 00:01:09,200
Look who’s talking.

21
00:01:09,560 --> 00:01:10,560
Why?

22
00:01:11,060 --> 00:01:13,632
Didn’t you also act like
it was a romance movie last night?

23
00:01:13,656 --> 00:01:14,560
What did I do?

24
00:01:14,600 --> 00:01:18,568
“Can you kiss me
while looking into my eyes?”

25
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:20,070
Stop exaggerating!

26
00:01:20,420 --> 00:01:23,136
“I want to see your eyes when we kiss.”

27
00:01:23,184 --> 00:01:24,376
You want to do this, huh?

28
00:01:24,384 --> 00:01:24,808
Oh!

29
00:01:24,824 --> 00:01:25,688
You want to do this, huh?

30
00:01:25,712 --> 00:01:27,080
It's so romantic.

31
00:01:27,120 --> 00:01:28,448
You want to do this, huh?

32
00:01:28,488 --> 00:01:30,768
Someone said this last night:

33
00:01:31,660 --> 00:01:33,568
“Your lips are so soft.”

34
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:36,168
“I’ve never felt anyone's lips this soft.”

35
00:01:39,660 --> 00:01:41,000
They really are soft.

36
00:01:41,032 --> 00:01:42,336
I wasn’t lying.

37
00:01:50,420 --> 00:01:52,088
And your eyes are really beautiful.

38
00:01:52,810 --> 00:01:54,512
Then I guess…

39
00:01:57,460 --> 00:01:59,768
we should call the professor.

40
00:02:02,952 --> 00:02:04,296
Hello, Professor Jui.

41
00:02:04,690 --> 00:02:07,200
Phi and I might be a bit late today.

42
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:08,744
We have something important to do.

43
00:02:09,970 --> 00:02:11,336
We have to go.
We’re in a hurry.

44
00:02:12,408 --> 00:02:14,410
You’re going to get it!

45
00:02:14,900 --> 00:02:16,192
What are you doing?

46
00:02:16,890 --> 00:02:17,704
Stop it!

47
00:02:17,712 --> 00:02:19,064
Gotcha!

48
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:43,288
Don’t tell me

49
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:46,192
you woke up just to stare at my face.

50
00:02:46,740 --> 00:02:47,740
Why not?

51
00:02:48,670 --> 00:02:50,896
I just feel like

52
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:54,808
you look a lot older.

53
00:02:54,848 --> 00:02:55,848
Shut up.

54
00:02:57,150 --> 00:02:58,630
You should find time to see a doctor.

55
00:02:59,220 --> 00:03:00,952
But I feel like

56
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:04,192
we still have it.

57
00:03:05,020 --> 00:03:07,768
Even though you say we’re older,

58
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:10,952
last night was pretty fire.

59
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:15,480
Then…

60
00:03:18,170 --> 00:03:19,352
we should call Yong.

61
00:03:23,350 --> 00:03:24,664
Hello, Yong.

62
00:03:24,696 --> 00:03:27,280
Phi and I are taking the day off today.

63
00:03:27,304 --> 00:03:29,496
I meant we should call him about work.

64
00:03:29,512 --> 00:03:32,520
Ask for feedback on our first episode.

65
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,896
Don’t tell me you got carried away.

66
00:03:43,170 --> 00:03:44,776
We’re adults.

67
00:03:45,060 --> 00:03:46,568
It’s a win-win for both of us.

68
00:03:47,260 --> 00:03:50,192
Think of it as a celebration of our show.

69
00:03:51,312 --> 00:03:52,312
That’s it.

70
00:04:01,050 --> 00:04:02,464
I’m going to take a shower.

71
00:04:08,980 --> 00:04:09,980
Here.

72
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,824
Hey!

73
00:04:59,340 --> 00:05:00,952
Why did you come in?

74
00:05:01,408 --> 00:05:03,008
To take a shower.

75
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:04,560
I have to go to work too.

76
00:05:04,608 --> 00:05:05,912
I’m already in the shower.

77
00:05:05,936 --> 00:05:07,328
You should wait.

78
00:05:07,344 --> 00:05:09,288
Well, you didn’t lock the door.

79
00:05:09,312 --> 00:05:10,864
If I were an overthinker,

80
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:12,616
I’d think you’re trying to seduce me.

81
00:05:13,100 --> 00:05:16,032
Luckily, I’m not.

82
00:05:16,570 --> 00:05:17,570
You don’t mind, right?

83
00:05:19,780 --> 00:05:21,360
Hand me the towel.

84
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:31,360
If you’re not an overthinker,

85
00:05:31,980 --> 00:05:33,312
we could shower together.

86
00:05:41,860 --> 00:05:43,264
You can look.

87
00:05:43,670 --> 00:05:46,048
It’s a win-win like you said.

88
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:47,704
Shall we shower together?

89
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:49,976
I’m already done.

90
00:05:56,820 --> 00:05:59,336
That thing of yours isn’t much to look at.

91
00:07:15,850 --> 00:07:16,816
What?

92
00:07:16,856 --> 00:07:18,472
My car broke down.

93
00:07:18,496 --> 00:07:20,470
I need a ride to work today.

94
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:21,640
Why?

95
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:23,976
If you don’t feel anything for me,

96
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,760
this shouldn’t be a problem, right?

97
00:07:43,250 --> 00:07:44,250
It’s stuck.

98
00:07:45,780 --> 00:07:46,448
Can you help me put it on?

99
00:07:46,472 --> 00:07:47,480
Seriously?

100
00:07:54,210 --> 00:07:55,504
Fine.

101
00:08:01,410 --> 00:08:02,624
I’ll put it on for you.

102
00:08:04,370 --> 00:08:05,560
You don’t know how to do it, huh?

103
00:08:05,584 --> 00:08:06,584
Mmm.

104
00:08:16,190 --> 00:08:17,936
Hmm.

105
00:08:17,968 --> 00:08:21,096
Is it tight down here?

106
00:08:45,670 --> 00:08:49,304
(We’re back with Talk to Top.)

107
00:08:49,330 --> 00:08:52,088
(We’re with a rising young businessman)

108
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:55,528
(who owns a lot of major real estate.)

109
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:57,790
(Paul Puttipat Issariyakul.)

110
00:08:57,808 --> 00:08:59,264
(He’s here with us now.)

111
00:08:59,288 --> 00:08:59,760
(Hi, Paul.)

112
00:08:59,792 --> 00:09:00,720
Paul.

113
00:09:00,752 --> 00:09:01,408
(Hi.)

114
00:09:01,432 --> 00:09:03,312
(Hi, everyone listening.)

115
00:09:03,340 --> 00:09:09,400
(Your interview with us last year received even better feedback than we expected.)

116
00:09:09,432 --> 00:09:11,390
(With your trustworthy image and…)

117
00:09:15,740 --> 00:09:18,320
So, have you found a club
you’re interested in?

118
00:09:18,368 --> 00:09:20,320
Let me guess.

119
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:22,320
You want to join the journalism club.

120
00:09:22,770 --> 00:09:25,760
Since you know me so well, why don’t you move to the same club as me?

121
00:09:25,792 --> 00:09:28,736
I’m telling you, if you want to find a partner,

122
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:31,320
find someone
who knows you as well as I do.

123
00:09:31,860 --> 00:09:32,860
Hey.

124
00:09:35,560 --> 00:09:36,768
Have you joined a club yet?

125
00:09:39,540 --> 00:09:41,088
Oh, not yet.

126
00:09:41,128 --> 00:09:42,824
That’s great.

127
00:09:42,848 --> 00:09:44,800
I heard your voice.
It’s really good.

128
00:09:44,824 --> 00:09:45,696
Are you sure?

129
00:09:45,728 --> 00:09:46,848
Yeah.

130
00:09:46,888 --> 00:09:48,032
That’s what I’m talking about.

131
00:09:48,056 --> 00:09:48,712
Thanks.

132
00:09:48,728 --> 00:09:50,536
I’m in the broadcasting club.

133
00:09:50,560 --> 00:09:52,064
Wanna give it a try?

134
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:53,328
Sure, why not?

135
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:55,616
Wow, your voice is so good.

136
00:09:55,656 --> 00:09:56,520
You could totally be a DJ.

137
00:09:56,521 --> 00:09:57,976
Can I try?

138
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:58,688
Come on.

139
00:09:58,728 --> 00:09:59,512
Careful, it’s raining.

140
00:09:59,536 --> 00:10:00,536
Thank you.
Come on.

141
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:05,352
Give it a shot.

142
00:10:05,368 --> 00:10:06,840
This is the controller.

143
00:10:07,070 --> 00:10:08,070
Oh, okay.

144
00:10:08,096 --> 00:10:09,096
Got it.

145
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:29,120
I’m here!

146
00:10:30,180 --> 00:10:31,376
Sorry I’m late.

147
00:10:31,416 --> 00:10:31,952
It’s alright.

148
00:10:31,976 --> 00:10:35,376
The broadcasting club asked me
to help with their new jingle.

149
00:10:35,408 --> 00:10:37,920
It’s for Paul’s show.

150
00:10:39,060 --> 00:10:40,072
It’s starting.

151
00:10:41,180 --> 00:10:41,936
Is this what you recorded?

152
00:10:41,944 --> 00:10:42,984
Yeah.

153
00:10:43,230 --> 00:10:44,488
Hold on.

154
00:10:45,090 --> 00:10:46,090
Let’s put on earphones.

155
00:10:47,140 --> 00:10:48,140
Here.

156
00:10:55,180 --> 00:10:57,016
(We’re in our second hour.)

157
00:10:57,048 --> 00:11:01,736
(Let’s hear from some teens
going through relationship problems)

158
00:11:01,776 --> 00:11:04,208
(and give them space
to vent their feelings.)

159
00:11:04,248 --> 00:11:06,552
I made this jingle.
Isn’t it cool?

160
00:11:06,576 --> 00:11:06,992
This one?

161
00:11:07,008 --> 00:11:07,880
Yeah.

162
00:11:07,920 --> 00:11:12,536
(Our first call is with Kao.)

163
00:11:13,010 --> 00:11:14,424
Hi, Kao.

164
00:11:14,448 --> 00:11:19,072
What do you want to share with us today?

165
00:11:20,260 --> 00:11:21,544
(Hi, Paul.)

166
00:11:21,584 --> 00:11:27,584
(Actually, I just wanted to call
and tell my best friend that I like him.)

167
00:11:27,744 --> 00:11:33,232
(But I can’t say it to him directly
because he’s also a man.)

168
00:11:33,248 --> 00:11:34,824
(I’m scared I’ll lose him.)

169
00:11:35,610 --> 00:11:38,096
(Oh.)

170
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:41,128
(Listen to me, Kao.)

171
00:11:42,020 --> 00:11:48,672
No best friend would stop being friends with you because you’re gay.

172
00:11:49,380 --> 00:11:56,800
(And if he’s open enough, your confession might lead to a happy ending.)

173
00:11:57,640 --> 00:12:02,848
(Love is too pure to be judged by gender.)

174
00:12:03,390 --> 00:12:04,390
(Do you understand?)

175
00:12:04,712 --> 00:12:07,112
(Just leave your fear behind.)

176
00:12:07,860 --> 00:12:11,096
(No matter what you choose to do, )

177
00:12:11,128 --> 00:12:12,496
(things will work out.)

178
00:12:12,528 --> 00:12:13,696
(Give it a try, Kao.)

179
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:15,540
Didn’t Paul give such a good answer?

180
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:17,952
He’s so cool.

181
00:12:22,110 --> 00:12:23,110
Phi…

182
00:12:24,256 --> 00:12:26,260
If something like that happened to you,

183
00:12:26,710 --> 00:12:27,710
what would you do?

184
00:12:29,150 --> 00:12:32,608
I’d do what Paul said.

185
00:12:32,910 --> 00:12:38,568
Love is too pure to be judged by gender.

186
00:12:40,260 --> 00:12:41,260
That’s really amazing.

187
00:12:42,450 --> 00:12:43,872
What do you think?

188
00:12:46,750 --> 00:12:49,768
Well… I agree with you.

189
00:12:50,270 --> 00:12:51,752
It’s true, right?

190
00:12:51,776 --> 00:12:52,776
Yeah.

191
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:57,176
Tam!

192
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:58,200
Huh?

193
00:12:58,670 --> 00:12:59,670
What?

194
00:13:01,870 --> 00:13:03,464
I’m getting out now.

195
00:13:03,488 --> 00:13:04,808
You can follow me later.

196
00:13:05,580 --> 00:13:06,580
Okay.

197
00:13:38,848 --> 00:13:39,824
Phi.

198
00:13:39,856 --> 00:13:40,856
Hmm?

199
00:13:41,060 --> 00:13:42,160
You forgot your badge.

200
00:13:45,792 --> 00:13:46,792
Thank you.

201
00:13:53,780 --> 00:13:55,256
You’re going to forget it again.

202
00:13:56,270 --> 00:13:57,856
Why don’t you wear it?

203
00:14:00,264 --> 00:14:02,400
Here, wear it.

204
00:14:03,220 --> 00:14:04,580
Otherwise, you’ll forget it again.

205
00:14:04,860 --> 00:14:05,860
Got it?

206
00:14:08,730 --> 00:14:10,280
You’re nagging me like a mom.

207
00:14:10,304 --> 00:14:11,304
Oh!

208
00:14:11,952 --> 00:14:12,952
I’m swooning!

209
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:14,712
Are you having a moment?

210
00:14:16,710 --> 00:14:19,864
Sorry to interrupt, old flames.

211
00:14:22,420 --> 00:14:23,840
What old flames?

212
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:27,080
Come on, Rita.

213
00:14:31,490 --> 00:14:35,744
Tam, I think he’s acting weird.

214
00:14:38,060 --> 00:14:39,200
How?

215
00:14:39,330 --> 00:14:45,040
Usually, Phi would play along with jokes,

216
00:14:45,590 --> 00:14:48,936
but whenever someone talks about you,

217
00:14:48,968 --> 00:14:52,400
he gets really serious.

218
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:56,784
Hey, does this mean…

219
00:14:57,030 --> 00:15:01,032
old flames are about to burn bright?

220
00:15:01,048 --> 00:15:03,208
Tam and Phi. Phi and Tam.

221
00:15:03,232 --> 00:15:04,232
Oh!

222
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:06,536
Nothing is going on.

223
00:15:06,568 --> 00:15:07,944
He and I…

224
00:15:08,990 --> 00:15:10,656
We’re just working together.

225
00:15:12,050 --> 00:15:13,050
Okay.

226
00:15:17,930 --> 00:15:19,032
Work?

227
00:15:21,370 --> 00:15:22,392
Then why did you smile?

228
00:15:27,100 --> 00:15:29,840
Actually, everyone really loves your demo.

229
00:15:30,570 --> 00:15:32,312
Yes!

230
00:15:35,730 --> 00:15:36,730
But…

231
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:38,720
But…

232
00:15:39,170 --> 00:15:40,872
we have no sponsors,

233
00:15:40,896 --> 00:15:42,870
so the board isn’t sure about it.

234
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,360
I knew it.

235
00:15:45,790 --> 00:15:48,600
If the show doesn’t go on air,
how will the sponsors see it?

236
00:15:49,090 --> 00:15:52,440
I’m sure once they do,
it’ll be easy to get their sponsorship.

237
00:15:52,464 --> 00:15:55,072
If no one sponsors us, does that mean

238
00:15:55,088 --> 00:15:56,840
our show will be put on hold?

239
00:15:58,140 --> 00:15:59,312
You have to understand,

240
00:15:59,328 --> 00:16:02,392
making a show isn’t cheap.

241
00:16:06,180 --> 00:16:07,180
It’s okay.

242
00:16:07,680 --> 00:16:09,376
Phi.

243
00:16:09,888 --> 00:16:10,936
Oh, Phi?

244
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:14,448
Wait, Tam.

245
00:16:14,488 --> 00:16:15,400
Where are you going?

246
00:16:15,416 --> 00:16:16,384
I have something urgent.

247
00:16:16,400 --> 00:16:17,680
Please take care of things here.

248
00:16:33,890 --> 00:16:35,848
I’ll post to let Phi’s fans know that

249
00:16:35,880 --> 00:16:37,864
Phi has a new show coming out,

250
00:16:37,888 --> 00:16:41,008
but the sponsors are calling Phi
a fallen star and refuse to fund it,

251
00:16:41,032 --> 00:16:44,280
which is why it’s been put on hold.

252
00:16:44,312 --> 00:16:47,912
Once the fans find out, they’ll come together and start trending to support Phi.

253
00:16:47,928 --> 00:16:52,064
Then Phi will be back in the spotlight
with the hashtag #SupportPhi.

254
00:16:52,104 --> 00:16:54,992
Once Phi is in the spotlight again,
we’ll get sponsors

255
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:57,544
and the show can go on.

256
00:16:57,552 --> 00:17:00,640
And when the show goes on,
Phi will be happy!

257
00:17:01,890 --> 00:17:03,064
Does that sound good?

258
00:17:07,096 --> 00:17:09,504
I’m glad you’re trying to help

259
00:17:11,250 --> 00:17:13,048
but not like this!

260
00:17:13,910 --> 00:17:17,312
You can’t set up an operating base
to trend for Phi in my office.

261
00:17:17,328 --> 00:17:18,328
Shh!

262
00:17:18,620 --> 00:17:19,728
Stop complaining.

263
00:17:19,752 --> 00:17:21,368
You have to help us get this trending.

264
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:23,800
And you have to get your team to help too.

265
00:17:23,840 --> 00:17:25,352
Sound good? Yes.

266
00:17:25,384 --> 00:17:27,112
Because I’ve already told the fans.

267
00:17:28,130 --> 00:17:28,624
Hey!

268
00:17:28,648 --> 00:17:29,480
I have something to do.

269
00:17:29,504 --> 00:17:30,416
I have something to do.

270
00:17:30,456 --> 00:17:31,456
I have to go.

271
00:17:31,860 --> 00:17:32,496
Hey!

272
00:17:32,512 --> 00:17:33,656
Good.

273
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:36,624
I’ll use your phone to help us trend.

274
00:17:36,648 --> 00:17:37,648
Huh?

275
00:17:47,920 --> 00:17:49,136
Two badges?

276
00:17:50,310 --> 00:17:51,310
Yes.

277
00:17:54,580 --> 00:17:55,580
Thank you.

278
00:17:58,630 --> 00:17:59,728
Why are you here?

279
00:18:01,190 --> 00:18:03,088
I heard you couldn’t
convince other companies.

280
00:18:05,220 --> 00:18:05,944
So what?

281
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:07,192
Are you here to help?

282
00:18:07,832 --> 00:18:09,830
Just in case they don’t like you,

283
00:18:10,710 --> 00:18:12,350
I’ll be the one to convince them instead.

284
00:18:14,520 --> 00:18:15,520
Thanks.

285
00:18:23,040 --> 00:18:24,472
Damn, what’s going on

286
00:18:25,260 --> 00:18:26,144
We’ll be fine.

287
00:18:26,176 --> 00:18:27,312
We still have time.

288
00:18:27,328 --> 00:18:28,456
We don’t have time.

289
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:29,192
We’re here to ask for their money.

290
00:18:29,216 --> 00:18:30,424
We can’t keep them waiting.

291
00:18:34,312 --> 00:18:35,472
There’s only one option left.

292
00:18:35,930 --> 00:18:36,930
Let’s go.

293
00:18:37,300 --> 00:18:40,016
Phi, it’s on the 24th floor.

294
00:19:07,104 --> 00:19:08,104
Come on!

295
00:19:18,710 --> 00:19:21,024
Excuse me, you’re Mr. Padtaphi, right?

296
00:19:21,048 --> 00:19:24,200
My boss asked me to let you know
something urgent came up.

297
00:19:24,224 --> 00:19:26,520
He’ll need to reschedule your presentation.

298
00:19:26,544 --> 00:19:28,248
We’re so sorry.

299
00:19:33,270 --> 00:19:34,848
It’s alright.

300
00:19:34,888 --> 00:19:37,232
We can reschedule.

301
00:19:37,256 --> 00:19:38,424
Okay.

302
00:19:38,440 --> 00:19:39,592
Thank you.

303
00:19:50,850 --> 00:19:53,632
Thank you for coming to help, Rita.

304
00:19:53,648 --> 00:19:55,630
We really need your support
as a big account.

305
00:19:56,570 --> 00:19:57,648
Don’t worry about it.

306
00:19:57,672 --> 00:19:59,120
I’m in Phi’s fandom too.

307
00:19:59,144 --> 00:20:00,184
Let’s help each other out.

308
00:20:01,230 --> 00:20:03,872
Then let’s get this trending on X today.

309
00:20:09,340 --> 00:20:10,560
What are you guys doing?

310
00:20:11,980 --> 00:20:14,288
Where’s Yong?

311
00:20:14,320 --> 00:20:15,776
I was asked to come here.

312
00:20:15,808 --> 00:20:17,064
He went to see a girl,

313
00:20:17,072 --> 00:20:18,808
so we asked you to come instead.

314
00:20:19,840 --> 00:20:20,416
Here.

315
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:20,904
Hmm?

316
00:20:20,936 --> 00:20:23,360
The hashtag is #SupportPhi.

317
00:20:23,376 --> 00:20:24,448
Let’s start tweeting.

318
00:20:25,032 --> 00:20:26,464
Yes, Gaogie.

319
00:20:26,496 --> 00:20:30,744
The main fanbase account
wants 400k tweets.

320
00:20:30,760 --> 00:20:32,576
Hold on.

321
00:20:32,608 --> 00:20:34,456
What hashtag? What tweets?

322
00:20:34,480 --> 00:20:36,328
We’re helping Phi find sponsors.

323
00:20:36,368 --> 00:20:38,728
Without sponsors,
the show won’t air.

324
00:20:38,752 --> 00:20:40,912
Then we’ll be out of jobs,
Phi will be sad,

325
00:20:40,928 --> 00:20:43,640
and the earth fandom will be upset.

326
00:20:44,560 --> 00:20:46,240
Nonsense.

327
00:20:46,296 --> 00:20:48,830
Just posting isn’t enough.

328
00:20:49,570 --> 00:20:51,216
There’s a better way.

329
00:20:52,470 --> 00:20:53,470
What’s that?

330
00:20:56,280 --> 00:20:58,824
Phi used to encourage us.

331
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:01,824
Today, Phi needs our encouragement.

332
00:21:01,832 --> 00:21:03,820
Are we just going to do nothing?

333
00:21:03,840 --> 00:21:07,136
Everyone, we need all your support.

334
00:21:07,184 --> 00:21:08,912
We need all your energy.

335
00:21:08,928 --> 00:21:11,336
We need all of you to come back.

336
00:21:12,100 --> 00:21:15,288
Yes, let’s reunite.

337
00:21:15,620 --> 00:21:17,216
Let’s come home.

338
00:21:17,240 --> 00:21:19,648
Let’s help our Prince Phi

339
00:21:19,688 --> 00:21:21,280
make his comeback.

340
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:23,008
We got this!

341
00:21:24,872 --> 00:21:25,808
Sis!

342
00:21:25,860 --> 00:21:27,344
We can do it!

343
00:21:27,360 --> 00:21:28,840
We can do it!

344
00:21:28,890 --> 00:21:32,440
We can do it.
WE NEED YOUR SUPPORT.
SUPPORTPHI EARTHFANDOM

345
00:21:32,464 --> 00:21:33,390
I believe we can do it.

346
00:21:33,400 --> 00:21:34,728
(Please help us.)

347
00:21:34,768 --> 00:21:37,512
(The hashtag is #SupportPhi.)

348
00:21:37,528 --> 00:21:39,504
What?

349
00:21:39,810 --> 00:21:42,024
We only got 9,000 views.

350
00:21:42,040 --> 00:21:43,176
And what’s this?

351
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:46,072
The comments are full of spam ads.

352
00:21:46,088 --> 00:21:47,424
What should we do?

353
00:21:47,464 --> 00:21:49,144
We’ve already done so much.

354
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:50,528
Let it go.

355
00:21:50,880 --> 00:21:52,992
I guess we can’t bring the fandom back.

356
00:21:53,032 --> 00:21:54,990
No, I’ll keep going.

357
00:21:55,540 --> 00:21:58,024
Let’s come up with a new campaign, Rita.

358
00:21:58,064 --> 00:21:59,712
Well, I want to help,

359
00:21:59,728 --> 00:22:03,208
but I’ve skipped work all day.

360
00:22:04,370 --> 00:22:06,032
Are you going to leave me?

361
00:22:06,056 --> 00:22:08,200
I’m not leaving you.

362
00:22:08,232 --> 00:22:09,336
I’m not.

363
00:22:09,352 --> 00:22:10,616
Not at all.

364
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:11,648
I’m not leaving you.

365
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:14,736
But I have to make a living.

366
00:22:14,784 --> 00:22:16,728
- I’m rooting for you.
- Sis!

367
00:22:16,760 --> 00:22:17,488
- I’m rooting for you.
- No!

368
00:22:17,520 --> 00:22:18,384
Believe in yourself.

369
00:22:18,408 --> 00:22:19,400
- Sis!
- You can do it.

370
00:22:19,424 --> 00:22:20,064
You can do it.

371
00:22:20,088 --> 00:22:21,088
I’m rooting for you.

372
00:22:21,490 --> 00:22:23,064
Sis!

373
00:22:23,088 --> 00:22:24,296
No!

374
00:22:24,984 --> 00:22:26,328
What should we do?

375
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:28,424
Keep trying.

376
00:22:28,432 --> 00:22:29,536
I have to get back to work.

377
00:22:29,568 --> 00:22:30,440
Hey.

378
00:22:30,560 --> 00:22:31,560
Hey.

379
00:22:32,830 --> 00:22:33,856
Gie!

380
00:22:35,350 --> 00:22:36,848
Why am I the only one left?

381
00:22:38,800 --> 00:22:39,800
Let’s post more.

382
00:22:46,800 --> 00:22:47,800
Thank you.

383
00:22:51,296 --> 00:22:52,296
Ouch.

384
00:23:04,120 --> 00:23:05,728
Oh, no.

385
00:23:08,430 --> 00:23:09,464
Wear my shoes.

386
00:23:11,700 --> 00:23:13,256
You still have many places to go.

387
00:23:14,070 --> 00:23:15,160
It’s alright.

388
00:23:16,424 --> 00:23:18,420
I really want to help you.

389
00:23:19,860 --> 00:23:21,344
Don’t be so hard on me.

390
00:23:22,510 --> 00:23:23,510
Wear these.

391
00:23:24,860 --> 00:23:25,860
Take those off.

392
00:23:54,440 --> 00:23:55,872
Thank you for the shoes.

393
00:23:57,160 --> 00:23:58,584
They’re much more comfortable.

394
00:24:06,816 --> 00:24:09,680
Next time, before you accept anyone’s appointment, screen them for me first.

395
00:24:09,704 --> 00:24:11,944
If we sponsor that kind of reporter,

396
00:24:11,968 --> 00:24:13,488
we’ll get canceled too.

397
00:24:13,520 --> 00:24:15,016
I’m sorry, Boss.

398
00:24:22,450 --> 00:24:23,576
You heard that, right?

399
00:24:25,580 --> 00:24:26,580
Mmm.

400
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:30,776
It’s alright. If they’re not interested,

401
00:24:31,100 --> 00:24:32,100
we can go somewhere else.

402
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:36,208
Put the shoes on.

403
00:24:50,480 --> 00:24:52,208
Our show is doing

404
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:54,448
a new kind of marketing for farmers

405
00:24:54,472 --> 00:24:56,450
and addressing the root causes
of their problems.

406
00:24:56,680 --> 00:25:00,864
We improve, encourage,
and build on their strengths

407
00:25:00,896 --> 00:25:03,856
using our journalism experience

408
00:25:04,520 --> 00:25:08,592
to solve the right problems.

409
00:25:09,500 --> 00:25:11,280
Mr. Padtaphi, Mr. Tamtawan,

410
00:25:11,320 --> 00:25:12,992
you can come inside in 5 minutes.

411
00:25:13,016 --> 00:25:14,016
Okay.

412
00:25:22,810 --> 00:25:23,810
Am I good to go?

413
00:25:25,640 --> 00:25:26,640
You forgot the shoes.

414
00:25:27,780 --> 00:25:28,780
Oh, right.

415
00:25:55,580 --> 00:25:57,816
I don’t know how many times I’ve told you

416
00:26:00,580 --> 00:26:01,728
that you’re amazing.

417
00:26:02,880 --> 00:26:04,288
After everything said about you,

418
00:26:04,950 --> 00:26:08,392
the old you would’ve gotten mad,

419
00:26:08,416 --> 00:26:10,600
lost your temper, or given up.

420
00:26:12,980 --> 00:26:14,624
But now you’re smiling at me.

421
00:26:16,770 --> 00:26:17,770
Phi,

422
00:26:20,150 --> 00:26:22,600
don’t let anything distract you.

423
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:26,472
You can always get a second chance.

424
00:26:29,610 --> 00:26:30,696
Look at me.

425
00:26:31,560 --> 00:26:34,488
Someone gave me a second chance
to be a producer.

426
00:27:11,720 --> 00:27:13,720
No matter if they say yes or no today,

427
00:27:16,210 --> 00:27:20,288
you’ll always be a true journalist to me.

428
00:27:26,760 --> 00:27:27,768
Well…

429
00:27:30,336 --> 00:27:36,088
If I get sponsorship today,

430
00:27:37,870 --> 00:27:38,950
let’s have a meal together.

431
00:27:40,830 --> 00:27:41,830
Sure.

432
00:27:50,420 --> 00:27:52,584
Mr. Padtaphi, Mr. Tamtawan,
please have a seat.

433
00:27:52,600 --> 00:27:53,168
Thank you.

434
00:27:53,192 --> 00:27:54,192
Hello.

435
00:27:55,740 --> 00:27:56,740
Hello.

436
00:27:57,830 --> 00:28:00,128
Sorry, my meeting ran late.

437
00:28:06,544 --> 00:28:08,540
You had to wait for a long time, Phi.

438
00:28:12,960 --> 00:28:13,960
Paul.

439
00:28:22,648 --> 00:28:24,650
Some stickers are so hard to remove.

440
00:28:25,280 --> 00:28:28,376
Sorry, I’m just too popular.

441
00:28:28,980 --> 00:28:30,472
I really tried not to be.

442
00:28:31,220 --> 00:28:33,944
Maybe they just gave you leftover stickers.

443
00:28:39,490 --> 00:28:40,280
Hey!

444
00:28:40,312 --> 00:28:41,832
What are you doing?

445
00:28:41,856 --> 00:28:43,200
You can’t remove this one.

446
00:28:43,224 --> 00:28:43,920
Why not?

447
00:28:43,976 --> 00:28:46,856
It’s from Paul, okay?

448
00:28:47,330 --> 00:28:48,608
Stay away from it.

449
00:28:48,632 --> 00:28:50,144
Remove the other ones.

450
00:28:50,730 --> 00:28:52,056
I’m possessive of it.

451
00:28:52,096 --> 00:28:53,096
Yeah?

452
00:28:53,140 --> 00:28:54,336
He’s just Paul.

453
00:28:54,384 --> 00:28:55,464
Who are you?

454
00:28:55,480 --> 00:28:56,480
Papa.

455
00:28:56,610 --> 00:28:57,656
You really are strict.

456
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:07,640
I think I’m into him.

457
00:29:16,980 --> 00:29:18,288
It’s been so long.

458
00:29:20,470 --> 00:29:21,608
It really has.

459
00:29:24,520 --> 00:29:27,792
Thank you so much, Paul,

460
00:29:27,816 --> 00:29:29,984
and sorry for wasting your time.

461
00:29:30,008 --> 00:29:32,312
I’ll make a new deck

462
00:29:32,336 --> 00:29:34,800
and come back to present it to you.

463
00:29:36,800 --> 00:29:40,664
Actually, I think everyone likes your show,

464
00:29:41,120 --> 00:29:42,496
but my boss…

465
00:29:42,528 --> 00:29:43,528
I understand.

466
00:29:43,720 --> 00:29:45,920
No one wants to sponsor

467
00:29:46,460 --> 00:29:48,256
someone with a bad image like me.

468
00:29:49,390 --> 00:29:50,840
Come on.

469
00:29:51,112 --> 00:29:52,120
People will forget.

470
00:29:54,730 --> 00:29:56,440
Don’t be upset. Come on.

471
00:29:56,672 --> 00:29:57,848
Keep your energy up.

472
00:29:58,110 --> 00:29:59,064
Don’t be upset.

473
00:29:59,096 --> 00:30:00,096
You got this.

474
00:30:00,440 --> 00:30:01,440
Listen.

475
00:30:01,780 --> 00:30:03,464
You need to smile at yourself, okay?

476
00:30:03,488 --> 00:30:04,640
No matter what happens.

477
00:30:05,430 --> 00:30:06,072
Okay.

478
00:30:06,104 --> 00:30:06,928
Yes.

479
00:30:07,056 --> 00:30:08,056
That’s it.

480
00:30:08,150 --> 00:30:09,768
This is the Phi I know.

481
00:30:11,770 --> 00:30:12,770
Hold on.

482
00:30:13,870 --> 00:30:16,984
Actually, I have another company

483
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:17,960
I own with my friends.

484
00:30:18,008 --> 00:30:20,528
I think your show is right for that.

485
00:30:21,420 --> 00:30:23,168
You can make a new deck

486
00:30:23,200 --> 00:30:25,000
and present it to my friends.

487
00:30:25,032 --> 00:30:26,336
I’ll help talk to them for you.

488
00:30:26,368 --> 00:30:27,184
Really?

489
00:30:27,208 --> 00:30:28,208
Yes.

490
00:30:28,410 --> 00:30:30,104
Have I ever lied to you?

491
00:30:30,770 --> 00:30:32,232
Thank you so much.

492
00:30:36,824 --> 00:30:37,824
No worries.

493
00:30:40,580 --> 00:30:43,160
I’ll see you soon.

494
00:30:44,150 --> 00:30:44,736
Mmm.

495
00:30:44,776 --> 00:30:45,776
Bye.

496
00:30:46,780 --> 00:30:47,780
Let’s go.

497
00:31:07,720 --> 00:31:09,440
Hey, hey, hey!

498
00:31:10,330 --> 00:31:11,768
Eat slowly.

499
00:31:12,210 --> 00:31:13,210
Drink some water.

500
00:31:17,420 --> 00:31:18,432
I ate too fast.

501
00:31:19,520 --> 00:31:21,360
I just want to finish this
as soon as possible.

502
00:31:23,030 --> 00:31:24,240
Look.

503
00:31:24,950 --> 00:31:27,080
Paul’s face doesn’t age at all.

504
00:31:28,216 --> 00:31:29,216
Really?

505
00:31:29,430 --> 00:31:30,430
Yeah.

506
00:31:31,310 --> 00:31:36,848
I knew he’d be successful one day.

507
00:31:38,350 --> 00:31:40,032
He’s a business owner now.

508
00:31:40,056 --> 00:31:41,704
I thought you said you were in a hurry.

509
00:31:42,290 --> 00:31:43,728
Why are you talking so much?

510
00:31:45,024 --> 00:31:45,730
Oh.

511
00:31:45,984 --> 00:31:47,056
Why not?

512
00:31:51,420 --> 00:31:53,472
Hey, can you take a look?

513
00:31:53,860 --> 00:31:55,712
Which color do you like for this page?

514
00:32:00,380 --> 00:32:01,480
Dark red.

515
00:32:02,370 --> 00:32:07,016
