You call me old?

563
00:37:22,848 --> 00:37:25,120
You’re old too.

564
00:37:25,290 --> 00:37:28,792
You should open your heart
to someone else.

565
00:37:28,980 --> 00:37:31,736
Your youth and beauty won’t last forever.

566
00:37:31,776 --> 00:37:32,776
Please.

567
00:37:33,248 --> 00:37:35,200
How would I even find the time?

568
00:37:35,590 --> 00:37:38,616
Taking care of this girl took up
all my sleeping time.

569
00:37:59,900 --> 00:38:00,900
Well…

570
00:38:00,980 --> 00:38:02,672
How do I say it?

571
00:38:03,808 --> 00:38:05,810
My friends…

572
00:38:16,200 --> 00:38:18,200
have agreed to sponsor your show

573
00:38:19,720 --> 00:38:22,960
because of the over 500k posts
supporting you last night.

574
00:38:22,984 --> 00:38:24,130
That’s amazing.

575
00:38:24,350 --> 00:38:25,384
Really?

576
00:38:25,408 --> 00:38:26,056
Yeah.

577
00:38:26,088 --> 00:38:27,576
Thank you so much, Paul.

578
00:38:27,600 --> 00:38:28,672
Thank you.

579
00:38:29,630 --> 00:38:34,424
Do you want to have dinner
to celebrate tonight?

580
00:38:34,660 --> 00:38:35,660
Of course.

581
00:38:38,270 --> 00:38:43,648
Well, if I get sponsorship today,

582
00:38:45,360 --> 00:38:46,448
let’s have a meal together.

583
00:38:51,710 --> 00:38:52,688
You two go ahead.

584
00:38:52,728 --> 00:38:54,160
I have work this evening.

585
00:38:54,460 --> 00:38:55,460
Hey.

586
00:38:55,620 --> 00:38:58,320
Then we don’t have to go.

587
00:38:58,344 --> 00:38:59,464
I feel bad.

588
00:38:59,820 --> 00:39:02,072
It’s like I’m stealing
your boyfriend for dinner, Tam.

589
00:39:02,100 --> 00:39:05,232
Uh…

590
00:39:05,248 --> 00:39:06,272
No.

591
00:39:06,930 --> 00:39:07,992
We’re not together.

592
00:39:09,864 --> 00:39:10,496
What?

593
00:39:10,740 --> 00:39:13,496
Did I get it wrong all this time?

594
00:39:13,536 --> 00:39:14,960
I thought you two were together.

595
00:39:18,728 --> 00:39:19,728
Yeah.

596
00:39:21,440 --> 00:39:22,440
Oh.

597
00:39:23,248 --> 00:39:26,616
In that case, I need to
choose a good restaurant.

598
00:39:27,920 --> 00:39:28,520
See you later, Phi.

599
00:39:28,544 --> 00:39:29,544
Okay.

600
00:39:29,840 --> 00:39:30,840
Thank you.

601
00:39:38,100 --> 00:39:39,936
Finally!

602
00:39:43,176 --> 00:39:46,672
Hey, do you think

603
00:39:47,180 --> 00:39:49,968
Paul was acting weird?

604
00:39:50,340 --> 00:39:52,840
Why would he want to know
if we’re together?

605
00:39:53,976 --> 00:39:58,016
He was checking because he likes you.

606
00:39:58,730 --> 00:40:00,064
Really?

607
00:40:01,350 --> 00:40:02,600
That’s too bad.

608
00:40:03,352 --> 00:40:05,350
What should we do if he likes me?

609
00:40:08,330 --> 00:40:09,728
Nothing.

610
00:40:10,190 --> 00:40:11,600
Isn’t that a good thing?

611
00:40:12,310 --> 00:40:14,824
We came here to make him like you.

612
00:40:15,480 --> 00:40:16,872
You got work done

613
00:40:17,460 --> 00:40:18,864
and your dream came true.

614
00:40:22,720 --> 00:40:23,824
Hey, wait, where are you going?

615
00:40:23,848 --> 00:40:25,232
My car is over there.

616
00:40:26,610 --> 00:40:28,240
I don’t want to be a third wheel.

617
00:40:28,264 --> 00:40:29,696
I’ll get a taxi.

618
00:40:54,730 --> 00:40:56,536
You’re bothering me so much!

619
00:40:56,560 --> 00:40:59,944
No, I’m not.

620
00:40:59,976 --> 00:41:01,112
No, I’m lazy.

621
00:41:01,136 --> 00:41:03,088
Come on, don’t be lazy.

622
00:41:03,136 --> 00:41:05,090
It’s not that hard.

623
00:41:05,128 --> 00:41:06,832
Please.

624
00:41:07,150 --> 00:41:08,744
Please record a clip for me.

625
00:41:08,784 --> 00:41:10,872
I’m auditioning to co-DJ with Paul.

626
00:41:10,904 --> 00:41:15,760
You can pretend to call
and ask for my advice.

627
00:41:16,510 --> 00:41:17,880
Please.

628
00:41:17,930 --> 00:41:21,104
Fine, but I won’t help you for free.

629
00:41:21,470 --> 00:41:22,384
Give me one week of free meals.

630
00:41:22,424 --> 00:41:24,672
I’ll give you two.

631
00:41:26,120 --> 00:41:27,120
Can we start now?

632
00:41:28,660 --> 00:41:29,792
I think so.

633
00:41:30,140 --> 00:41:31,140
Okay.

634
00:41:31,600 --> 00:41:34,824
What do you want me to call you about?

635
00:41:35,090 --> 00:41:37,208
Anything. Just improvise.

636
00:41:37,480 --> 00:41:37,960
Come on.

637
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:39,320
Fine.

638
00:41:40,640 --> 00:41:41,840
Recording starts in

639
00:41:42,430 --> 00:41:46,232
5, 4, 3, 2…

640
00:41:47,208 --> 00:41:49,552
We’re in our third hour, guys.

641
00:41:49,576 --> 00:41:53,552
Let’s answer some calls from our listeners.

642
00:41:54,384 --> 00:41:56,232
Beep. Beep.

643
00:41:56,264 --> 00:41:58,808
Beep. Beep. Beep.

644
00:42:00,810 --> 00:42:01,840
Hi, there.

645
00:42:01,896 --> 00:42:02,984
Hi.

646
00:42:03,900 --> 00:42:05,208
Make a proper sound.

647
00:42:06,950 --> 00:42:07,950
Hi.

648
00:42:08,550 --> 00:42:11,784
Hi, may I know who I’m speaking to?

649
00:42:14,020 --> 00:42:15,020
Tawan.

650
00:42:15,064 --> 00:42:17,304
Ah, Tawan.

651
00:42:17,336 --> 00:42:20,408
What would you like advice on today?

652
00:42:21,590 --> 00:42:25,256
It’s about…love.

653
00:42:25,296 --> 00:42:27,520
Oh, love.

654
00:42:27,560 --> 00:42:29,648
A teenage problem.

655
00:42:29,696 --> 00:42:31,650
Tell the doctor your symptoms.

656
00:42:35,050 --> 00:42:36,848
I have a crush on my best friend.

657
00:42:36,888 --> 00:42:37,888
Mmm.

658
00:42:38,232 --> 00:42:40,230
We didn’t really get along at first.

659
00:42:43,220 --> 00:42:45,392
He was like a nuisance to me,

660
00:42:45,424 --> 00:42:48,328
always causing trouble
and asking me to fix it.

661
00:42:49,400 --> 00:42:51,448
But as we got to know each other

662
00:42:51,920 --> 00:42:53,744
over time and I saw him grow up,

663
00:42:53,776 --> 00:42:55,080
somehow I became happy.

664
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:57,224
Before I knew it,

665
00:42:58,900 --> 00:43:00,072
I’d fallen for him.

666
00:43:02,240 --> 00:43:03,232
But to him,

667
00:43:03,264 --> 00:43:06,840
I’m probably just a friend
who supports him.

668
00:43:08,840 --> 00:43:14,856
Do you think I should tell him how I feel

669
00:43:16,220 --> 00:43:20,208
or keep my feelings to myself
and keep being a good friend?

670
00:43:21,984 --> 00:43:23,980
Whoa.

671
00:43:25,040 --> 00:43:28,536
Hmm, I totally get it.

672
00:43:29,300 --> 00:43:36,456
I believe many of our viewers have been through what you’re going through, Tam.

673
00:43:36,950 --> 00:43:39,312
But if you ask me,

674
00:43:39,730 --> 00:43:41,392
I think…

675
00:43:43,190 --> 00:43:44,624
you should tell him.

676
00:43:44,940 --> 00:43:47,080
Who knows?

677
00:43:47,120 --> 00:43:50,790
He might be waiting to hear it.

678
00:44:07,710 --> 00:44:09,192
Hey, Tam!

679
00:44:09,576 --> 00:44:11,580
I’m going to report you to the NGOs.

680
00:44:11,608 --> 00:44:12,800
Go ahead.

681
00:44:14,860 --> 00:44:15,728
Are you okay?

682
00:44:15,760 --> 00:44:17,000
You're not in a very good mood.

683
00:44:18,860 --> 00:44:20,264
I’m fine.

684
00:44:20,288 --> 00:44:21,736
Can I help you with anything?

685
00:44:21,980 --> 00:44:23,920
Oh, I’m looking for Phi.

686
00:44:23,968 --> 00:44:24,784
Just wanted to ask

687
00:44:24,800 --> 00:44:26,780
if he was able
to get any sponsors for the show.

688
00:44:27,600 --> 00:44:28,904
Yes, he did.

689
00:44:28,944 --> 00:44:30,432
He’s out to celebrate right now.

690
00:44:31,020 --> 00:44:34,288
Oh, then why didn’t you follow him?

691
00:44:35,488 --> 00:44:37,490
I’m celebrating by myself.

692
00:44:46,410 --> 00:44:48,824
I think he wants to
celebrate alone with the client.

693
00:44:50,820 --> 00:44:52,820
They were senior and junior
in the same club.

694
00:44:53,290 --> 00:44:54,520
They’re close.

695
00:45:03,130 --> 00:45:10,672
Tam, I don’t know why you two
broke up or drifted apart,

696
00:45:10,696 --> 00:45:12,064
but from what I’ve seen,

697
00:45:12,510 --> 00:45:15,528
your bond can never be broken.

698
00:45:17,530 --> 00:45:19,136
Why do you think so?

699
00:45:20,910 --> 00:45:25,384
Think about it, Tam, if you had
no feelings for each other anymore.

700
00:45:26,720 --> 00:45:31,144
When the other person
did something good or bad,

701
00:45:31,810 --> 00:45:33,424
you wouldn’t care.

702
00:45:34,840 --> 00:45:36,192
You’d be indifferent.

703
00:45:36,680 --> 00:45:39,200
But from what I’ve seen,

704
00:45:39,240 --> 00:45:44,200
you two still care about
the little things about each other.

705
00:45:44,820 --> 00:45:46,592
You still want to scold

706
00:45:47,112 --> 00:45:49,528
and smile at each other.

707
00:46:04,850 --> 00:46:06,090
DON’T LET ME CATCH YOU SMILING.

708
00:46:11,520 --> 00:46:12,840
He’s just an ex.

709
00:46:13,740 --> 00:46:15,840
Yes, he’s just an ex,

710
00:46:16,450 --> 00:46:19,640
but I want you to think carefully.

711
00:46:20,960 --> 00:46:24,568
Deep down, how do you feel
about this ex?

712
00:46:31,940 --> 00:46:32,840
DEMO: TEENAGE LOVE TROUBLES
BY PADTAPHI

713
00:46:32,864 --> 00:46:33,864
Here you go.

714
00:46:38,730 --> 00:46:39,730
What?

715
00:46:41,910 --> 00:46:43,400
Nothing.

716
00:46:45,560 --> 00:46:46,872
Root for me.

717
00:46:49,980 --> 00:46:50,980
Yeah.

718
00:46:55,420 --> 00:47:02,328
(You should tell him. Who knows?
(He might be waiting to hear it.)

719
00:47:06,330 --> 00:47:07,330
Phi.

720
00:47:07,880 --> 00:47:08,880
Hey, Phi.

721
00:47:09,500 --> 00:47:10,660
I have something to tell you.

722
00:47:21,590 --> 00:47:22,590
Phi!

723
00:47:33,480 --> 00:47:34,480
What?

724
00:47:36,380 --> 00:47:39,672
Nothing.

725
00:47:52,070 --> 00:47:53,070
Tam!

726
00:48:11,570 --> 00:48:12,680
Tell me honestly.

727
00:48:13,880 --> 00:48:15,144
Why did you come back?

728
00:48:16,230 --> 00:48:17,230
Hey!

729
00:48:22,840 --> 00:48:25,912
I want my show up on a billboard like that.

730
00:48:25,960 --> 00:48:30,144
And I only want you to be
the one who makes it happen.

731
00:48:31,496 --> 00:48:33,500
You can always get a second chance.

732
00:48:34,090 --> 00:48:35,168
Look at me.

733
00:48:35,980 --> 00:48:38,832
Someone gave me a second chance
to become a producer.

734
00:48:38,864 --> 00:48:39,864
Here.

735
00:48:40,250 --> 00:48:41,696
Yong asked me to give you this.

736
00:48:42,670 --> 00:48:44,280
Take good care of it

737
00:48:44,960 --> 00:48:46,960
and don’t leave me again this time,

738
00:48:47,700 --> 00:48:49,024
Mr. Producer.

739
00:48:53,150 --> 00:48:54,216
Okay.

740
00:48:55,270 --> 00:48:56,270
Tam,

741
00:48:59,980 --> 00:49:01,760
don’t get go of Phi’s hand.

742
00:49:05,190 --> 00:49:08,000
Right now,

743
00:49:08,040 --> 00:49:09,568
you’re the only one who can help him.

744
00:49:10,180 --> 00:49:11,712
If you still love him,

745
00:49:12,410 --> 00:49:13,560
come back.

746
00:49:14,160 --> 00:49:15,864
I know he’s my ex.

747
00:49:17,860 --> 00:49:21,280
But he’s the ex I want to
start over with the most.

748
00:49:49,760 --> 00:49:51,112
Hello, Paul.

749
00:49:51,960 --> 00:49:53,544
Yes, I’ve arrived.

750
00:49:53,560 --> 00:49:54,840
I’m about to go inside.

751
00:49:55,540 --> 00:49:56,540
Okay.

752
00:49:57,980 --> 00:49:58,980
Phi.

753
00:49:59,790 --> 00:50:02,552
Oh, why are you here?

754
00:50:05,360 --> 00:50:06,360
I…

755
00:50:11,880 --> 00:50:12,880
Nothing.

756
00:50:16,024 --> 00:50:18,640
Let’s talk later then.

757
00:50:18,664 --> 00:50:19,752
I’m going inside.

758
00:50:21,410 --> 00:50:22,792
Don’t go.

759
00:50:28,504 --> 00:50:30,432
I know you’ve liked him for a long time

760
00:50:32,728 --> 00:50:34,730
and I know you still like him now.

761
00:50:37,470 --> 00:50:39,688
I know he’s better than me in every way.

762
00:50:41,020 --> 00:50:42,648
He’s smarter than me.

763
00:50:42,920 --> 00:50:44,650
He’s more handsome than me.

764
00:50:46,220 --> 00:50:48,112
He’s freaking taller than me.

765
00:50:48,144 --> 00:50:49,216
You know that.

766
00:51:00,200 --> 00:51:01,200
Yes.

767
00:51:02,300 --> 00:51:04,024
If you know that, why are you here?

768
00:51:07,540 --> 00:51:10,192
Because I know that
even though he beats me in every way,

769
00:51:11,340 --> 00:51:13,656
he’ll never know you better than I do.

770
00:51:17,660 --> 00:51:19,080
I know you snore.

771
00:51:19,096 --> 00:51:20,680
I know you like the color red.

772
00:51:21,096 --> 00:51:23,100
I know eating chocolate
puts you in a good mood.

773
00:51:23,144 --> 00:51:25,512
I know your shoe size is 42.5

774
00:51:25,552 --> 00:51:29,328
I know you always keep Do Not Disturb on because you don’t like anyone calling you.

775
00:51:33,420 --> 00:51:37,432
I know you still can’t forget me.

776
00:51:42,140 --> 00:51:43,808
I won’t give up this time.

777
00:51:45,488 --> 00:51:47,490
I’ll fight to win you back.

778
00:51:56,680 --> 00:52:00,624
I think there’s still one thing
you don’t know.

779
00:52:04,110 --> 00:52:08,792
I told Paul I liked him.

780
00:52:17,616 --> 00:52:19,620
And I told him

781
00:52:23,144 --> 00:52:25,140
he and I can only be brothers.

782
00:52:31,410 --> 00:52:32,410
Why?

783
00:52:41,580 --> 00:52:42,592
Because I…

784
00:52:46,590 --> 00:52:48,312
I guess I still can’t forget my ex.

785
00:52:56,980 --> 00:53:00,616
Heard it many times, how love’s a beautiful thing

786
00:53:00,664 --> 00:53:03,112
So full of meaning

787
00:53:05,136 --> 00:53:06,520
Having someone is good for the soul

788
00:53:06,544 --> 00:53:10,744
It fills the space and makes your heart whole

789
00:53:10,784 --> 00:53:14,328
It makes you tremble, makes you shy

790
00:53:14,376 --> 00:53:16,792
It paints the world so bright

791
00:53:16,816 --> 00:53:20,184
Having someone who will always be there

792
00:53:20,208 --> 00:53:23,832
It makes you smile, that's what they say

793
00:53:23,864 --> 00:53:25,328
LET ME HELP SO YOU CAN REST.

794
00:53:25,368 --> 00:53:29,800
I only knew the truth when love led me to you

795
00:53:29,832 --> 00:53:32,040
If you think you know me well,

796
00:53:33,260 --> 00:53:34,856
then you should know that

797
00:53:36,500 --> 00:53:38,240
ever since you came back,

798
00:53:39,780 --> 00:53:41,880
my life hasn’t been the same.

799
00:53:45,450 --> 00:53:48,296
But if you think you know me best,

800
00:53:49,320 --> 00:53:50,848
I don’t think so.

801
00:53:52,020 --> 00:53:53,640
I used to think that way.

802
00:53:59,510 --> 00:54:01,992
I used to think I knew you best,

803
00:54:04,500 --> 00:54:06,144
but I didn’t.

804
00:54:14,740 --> 00:54:18,760
So, I want us to

805
00:54:21,000 --> 00:54:23,128
keep getting to know each other.

806
00:54:27,936 --> 00:54:29,940
Do you want to get back together?

807
00:54:39,940 --> 00:54:42,480
I’ve been waiting to hear that, you know?

808
00:54:46,728 --> 00:54:53,230
Damn, we’re funny.

809
00:54:54,270 --> 00:54:57,840
It’s like we’re straight out of a romcom

810
00:54:58,820 --> 00:55:02,736
about exes who hate each other.

811
00:55:03,380 --> 00:55:04,992
But have to see each other again?

812
00:55:09,980 --> 00:55:14,856
To prove that no one is better than

813
00:55:16,860 --> 00:55:17,860
this ex.

814
00:55:24,400 --> 00:55:25,960
I don’t think we’re like that.

815
00:55:27,300 --> 00:55:29,856
If we really were in a romcom,

816
00:55:31,070 --> 00:55:32,464
right now we’d be…

817
00:55:34,630 --> 00:55:35,630
You’re right.

818
00:55:37,400 --> 00:55:38,592
What are we waiting for?

819
00:55:42,010 --> 00:55:50,010
Will there be a new ending for me to find?

820
00:55:50,960 --> 00:55:54,176
Tell me now, be kind

821
00:55:54,220 --> 00:55:58,256
Did you return to make it right?

822
00:55:58,288 --> 00:56:01,912
A renewal

823
00:56:05,310 --> 00:56:08,176
Tell me now, be kind

824
00:56:08,200 --> 00:56:13,320
DIRECTED BY PHADUNG SAMAJARN
Did you return to make it right?

825
00:56:13,352 --> 00:56:14,680
What are you doing today?

826
00:56:15,160 --> 00:56:17,400
Shall we take Sosay to the beach?

827
00:56:17,424 --> 00:56:20,016
Someone sneaked a cat into the office, right?

828
00:56:20,056 --> 00:56:20,776
Where are you going? Come here!

829
00:56:20,808 --> 00:56:21,544
-Sosay!

830
00:56:21,568 --> 00:56:22,200
LET’S BREAK UP.

831
00:56:22,232 --> 00:56:26,104
Yong told me that Tam loves you very much, Phi.

832
00:56:26,136 --> 00:56:27,272
When you were gone,

833
00:56:27,296 --> 00:56:29,270
I had a question I always wanted to ask you.

834
00:56:29,304 --> 00:56:31,744
I found out why you left me that day.

835
00:56:32,510 --> 00:56:34,816
I hate you!
